The Bank of Japan intervened just afterthe Tokyo market opened, buying dollars at around 147.65 yen,dealers said.    They were unsure of the amount of the central bank'spurchasing, but it seemed to prevent the dollar from weakeningagainst the yen amid bearish sentiment for the U.S. Currency,they said.    The dollar opened at 147.65 yen against 147.20/30 in NewYork and 146.90 at the close here yesterday. REUTER&#3;